annotation.TEXT: Didn't I check this odd dirt already?
That unlocks 3-2, but 3-1 has a secret exit for me to find somewhere...
That would've been a neat place to put a multi-coin block.
Will I make it?
That's right! I'm using it for fun in the already cleared 2-2! This gives all those shells at the start of this level some decent use!
And, all of a sudden, I'm in a forest, and there's a midpoint.

Oh, hey there Lakitu. Now, because fireballs just outright destroy enemies in this hack rather than turn them into coins, frying Lakitu will not remove him permanently or give me an unlimited cloud. (I can certainly still fry him, of course.)
Yeah, I can stomp Bullet Bills no problem while I'm in a cloud (as long as I'm not ascending).
Whoa. Almost pressed my luck too much there and just barely avoided the Whammy. Let's try that again.
And there's my secret exit.
Could this also maybe be the secret to the fifth star coin?
So, there are plenty of coins up here. Does this include a star coin anywhere?
Cool.
3♥P sun count: 4
Umm... Uh, oh. Maybe going under these blocks isn't a good idea!
Oh, well isn't that fortunate! I needed a shell to break that green block anyway!
I guess not. Let's move on.
Okay, now this time, grab one of the upper coins, but don't drop down yet!

And, that of course leads to 3-A. Now, even though I'm already 10 minutes into this video, the only new level I've played so far today is 3-1, and I'd like to do more than just that, so I'm going to head to 3-2 now.
Whoa, hello there Mr. Sun! Hey, that's a nice perfectly square cutoff you made in the land there! Also, there's a springboard that lets you bounce back up and try for a good goal tape hit.

Seriously, though. I mainly went under those ? blocks thinking that I'd need to continue the ballooning chain. Had I known that the ballooning segment ended there, I would've gone above those blocks instead.
And there's our fruit, but unfortunately, I've been told that there's no Yoshi in this hack. Aww...
No? Well, a shell jump will certainly work!
Too bad there's no coin pyramids down below for me to dive into. In fact, I think I just wasted that P-switch...

Yes, I just clipped through the slope there, doods. Good thing I had Start+Select available that time! (Also, this lets me show off the midpoint entrance, which I had correctly assumed was that pipe.)
Okay, fine. If you insist, I'll take the mushroom.
Hey, hey! Alright! That'll certainly improve my goal tape average! Now I just need 5 more of those to get my average above 40...
Goal tape average so far: 907 / 24 = 37.792 stars each.
And apparently, the air current pushed me into that block so hard that I collected its balloon instantly.
Ooh, we get to go on a balloon ride!
Huh... I wonder what's with the dirt here under this bush. Is it hiding a secret or something?
And there's Lakitu again. I wonder why Lakitu becomes immune to thrown weapons while he's throwing a spiny...
It's you!! How are you Hammer Brother. All your coin are belong to us. You have no chance to survive make your time.
Aha! A secret note block! But, wait! There's more! ...I think...
What? A tall wall? How do I get past that?
Yeah, the P-switch was quite obviously meant for over here.
Now, I'm wondering if I overlooked anything at ground level in this area...
There'd better be more!
Goal tape average so far: 987 / 26 = 37.962 stars each.
Are there more hidden note blocks to reach that feather with?
Oh, man. I've gotta chain balloons together? But, this is only world 3-1. It couldn't possibly be as nasty as the original game's Tubular... right?
What, did I suddenly forget where the second note block was for a moment?
Ooh, actual custom level music! The first two worlds have mostly just been using vanilla SMW music (except for world 1-House, and the Challenge Star levels).
Alright, so the voting choices this time are... 3-3...
Aw... I was late on the timing for the silly spin jump sound effect there.
BGM: RoboWarrior (NES) - Main Theme
Alright, I suppose that technically raises my average.
Probably an exit pipe from whatever cool areas I missed out on.
Oof! Failed to cape spin in time there.
I wonder if there was anything of interest in that pit...
Well, it's no surprise that 3-1 won this time, so let's head on over to Apple Country!
Ah. Found it. Start+Select!
So, vote for either 3-3, 3-A, or 5-1, and I'll start with the winner next time! To be continued...
Huh. Still no sign of that missing star coin, but it could be on the other side of this pipe...
Okay, to speed things up, I'm going to take to the skies in the balloon and use the left+right glitch to scan as much airspace as possible.
Well, this time, it's 28 coins made to look like an exclamation point. (I wonder if there was a hidden message up here all this time...)
Welp, so much for Mr. Glitchy Beetle. Okay, time for ludicrous speed!
Well, I correctly predicted that that pipe was a bonus room exit. But, I'm not done yet. Let's quickly go back for another P-switch...
There's the fourth star coin, and with that, I pass the million mark!
Huh, what's up here?
Okay, now at the end here, if you stand next to the goal, and look to the left...
50-star goal tape hits: 4 Goal tape average so far: 1037 / 27 = 38.407 stars each.
Let's see what kind of combo I can pull off here...
There's midpoint.
And I suppose that technically raises my bonus game average.
Okay, so that obviously wasn't the proper way to use the P-switch, doods.
A pipe that I probably should take now.
BGM: New Super Mario Bros. (DS) - Walking the Plains

Wow, still no star coin though? Two whole bonus side areas and neither one of them contain the star coin I was missing? I wonder if I missed it elsewhere, or if this is yet another level that short-changes me on the star coins...
Yes, because everyone should have the right to fart.
Ah, okay. I wonder why I didn't find that sooner...
This P-switch block setup reminds me of 2-3 of SMB3.
Gee... I wonder what game that was from...
Goal tape average so far: 1077 / 28 = 38.464 stars each.
Oh, I just thought of something. Let me try carrying this Buzzy out of this side area...
I wonder how big a chain I can get from cape spinning this shell...
Okay, I finally managed to tag him.
I don't know why I felt like making that reference there.
Heck, yeah. Tap dancing on Chucks.
ICE BLOCKS!!!!!
Also, there was no way that I was going to be able to get through that passage without ending the stomping chain back there.
Ugh. It's that dreaded "Hurry Up!" warning again...
Bonus game average so far: 75 / 10 = 7.5 1♥Ps each.
...and the "!" formation...
Oh, and we've got air currents here.
There's that "X" formation I found before...
I wonder how far I can keep this stomping chain going...
Ow. That was just me being stupid.
Okay, so what I guess you're supposed to do is, instead of taking to the skies with the balloon, stay down low and float to that pipe, like this.
Also, there's apparently a ceiling just off screen here.
And now let's see what's down here...
Whoa, hello there third hidden note block that I somehow didn't uncover until now!
...And my cloud ran out of gas. So, I saw "♥MX!"... I wonder if that means anything... (Oh, and I checked back later, and there's nothing else in the sky that I haven't already seen here.)
Another side area, so I guess you'd need to backtrack for a second P-switch no matter what if you wanted to visit both side areas in this level in one trip.
There's what looks like an "M"... maybe.
Argh, and I also broke the chain. At least I get my cape back, though.
Whoa, I wonder how that Wiggler managed to fall down onto the munchers...
Yep, barely. That's a 4-life combo! Now, for the real reason I'm replaying 2-2, it turns out raocow found something in this level that I did not, so I'm here to show that off.
Lots of bubbled stuff here, including a mushroom that I don't need.
Well, nuts. I'm out of ideas. If this level does contain a fifth star coin, and anyone knows where it is, let me know!
Oh, I saw something up there. Oh, it's just 20 coins in a blocky "X" formation.
Also, we're doing some ballooning.
"L" says nope. Nothing but death.
At least this level has five star coins! I wonder why some levels like 2-5 only have four... Did the level maker simply forget to place the fifth one or something?

Hello, and welcome back to Super Marina World! First of all, thanks go to everyone that wished me a happy birthday two days ago. Now, remember how last time I said I'd only use the reserve star here if I died five times in a level, or just for fun in an already cleared level?
And during this Lakitu war, he uses his spiny-throwing immunity-to-thrown-stuff frames to great effect!
Okay, so I got a feather, which is cool, and now I'm gliding through updrafts.
Now, 3-1 is apparently called "Welcome! To the Country of the Fruit".
Bonus game average so far: 67 / 9 = 7.444 1♥Ps each.

Well, if it turns out that there's a secret somewhere that absolutely requires the reserve star to reach, then I'll also certainly use it in such a situation. Now, take a wild guess why I'm using the reserve star here!
Let's see how Buzzy likes clipping through a slope! (Insert evil laughter here.)
Ha! Mid-air cloud hijack FTW! And I can use left+right with the cloud too!
Well, who knows what stuff I ended up missing... Not a secret exit though, since this is a yellow level. Still, I'm probably going to replay the level just to use that P-switch properly.
That opens up 3-3. Now, let's go back to 3-2 and use that P-switch properly!
That's three lives. Can I get any more?
Well, that sucked... At least there's a flower right there that I can use.
Just a 1♥P. Nothing important.
And now let's check out those votes and see whether I head to 3-1 or 5-1 next...
Now, let's see if I can start raising my goal tape average...

Oh, over here, I think the proper way to solve this puzzle is to bounce off of Wiggler to get onto the turn block, instead of using the springboard to get up. This lets you carry the springboard past this wall, and that's probably how you're meant to get the next feather.
Wait, I saw something to the left...
Ooh, somewhat tricky star coin. Good thing I didn't roast that parakoopduder too soon!
Goal tape average so far: 947 / 25 = 37.88 stars each.
Did I use the correct number of asterisks in that "*Raises hand*" line?
Haw, haw! I thought that might happen. Buzzy Beetle is a tileset-specific sprite, and carrying it through a pipe into an area with a different sprite tileset will make it appear glitched like this!
Oh, there's a ♥ formation of coins that I didn't know about.
Of course, I am missing a star coin, but it's a good bet that proper usage of the P-switch at the start will lead me to it.
Whoa. I'm going to try to avoid accidentally using the left+right glitch for the most part.
Uh, I saw more stuff up above. It's probably just more coins, but let's see if I can hijack Lakitu's cloud and check it out...
Well, there's an obvious life-farming spot that I don't need. (Just kick a shell onto the ? blocks and then stand on the single cement block below while the shell kills bullets and spinies for you.)
That shell was obviously meant for the Hammer Brother, but I think I got him with my cape instead.

WHEW! Just barely made it! Pop quiz: What game was that frantic music I edited in from? First to answer correctly gets 10 happy smile points! (UPDATE: No one even took a guess at it, so here's the answer: Mole Mania for Game Boy.)

D'oh. I forgot. You can't stomp a land-based enemy that's on the ground while you're in a cloud for some stupid reason. (Flying enemies and enemies that are in mid-air actually are stompable while you're in a cloud though...)
